album.title: Best of Ella Fitzgerald & Louis Armstrong

track.name: Summertime
comments: hot...!  from pops opening trumpet blast...to ella's one-to-a-planet magnificent voice...to pops super jazzy voice...they were/are the greatest vocal jazz duet ever...(3)
Gives me chills, lyk my arm hairs literally raise anytime i hear dis
There just faultless, to listen to them is an education in it's self.

THE VERSION! Louis' trumpet intro alone makes this a classic. This is Ella at her best and Louis is his usual brilliant self. Guess what- this is one of my loved tracks. There are other good versions but they pale into insignificance when Ella and Satchmo begin.
Awesome song, that is definitely Louis Armstrong.
Correct me if im wrong but isn't that Duke Ellington's voice?
Wow !!! Hiper clásico, belleza sin limites.
I absolutely love this track.. I am yet to understand, however, why on earth Gershwin wrote it in a minor key?..
